*** Chapter 4

1) Arithmetic Operator : Arithmetic operators are used to perform common mathematical operations.
    Ex : + , -  , * , /.
    
2) Assignment Operator : Assignment operators are used to assign values to variables.
    Ex : int x = 10 ( = is assignment operator)'
    
3) Relational Operator : Relational operators are used to check the relationship between two operands.
    Ex : (> , < , <= , >= ,==).

4) Logical operator : Logical operators are used to determine the logic between variables or values
    Ex : AND , OR , NOT





*** Chapter 5 

1) labeled and unlabled statement.

	> break : is used to come out of the loop under certain condition. loop can be while loop or for loop etc.
	> continue : is opposite of break, this is used to skip the logic and start for the next sequence in under certain condition.
	
2) Exception : 	it is used to handle runtime error.we can use try, catch and throw for exception handling.
	
